President Muhammadu Buhari has paid a special condolence visit to the families of the nine persons who died from Kano Sabon Gari Gas Cylinder explosion. The president who was at the Emir Aminu Ado Bayeroâ€™s palace during the condolence visit, said he was in Kano for a national assignment but felt he should see them to sympathise with them. Speaking during the visit, Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje said his government had already provided N9 million to the families of the deceased. He said 27 persons were seriously injured and government had taken over the medical treatment, adding that the government had taken serious measures to prevent re-occurrence of similar incidence. The Emir of Kano, Alhaji Aminu Ado Bayero, thanked the president for the visit to the families of those who died from the gas cylinder blast at Sabon Gari. He said this signified the President`s concern and love for Nigerians, adding that his Emirate would continue to pray for peace and stability in the country. He commended the president for doing all he could to save Nigeria from collapse, and pray that the forthcoming general elections would be peaceful and Nigeria would have elected desired leaders like him who were so concerned with the growth and progress of the country.